            "id": "q1",
            "number": 1,
            "question": "Classify the following polynomials as polynomials in one variable, two variables etc.",
            "parts": [
                "(i) $x^2 + x + 1$",
                "(ii) $y^3 - 5y$",
                "(iii) $xy + yz + zx$",
                "(iv) $x^2 - 2xy + y^2 + 1$"
            ],
            "solution": "<ul><li>(i) $x^2 + x + 1$: Contains only one variable $x$. <strong>Polynomial in one variable.</strong></li><li>(ii) $y^3 - 5y$: Contains only one variable $y$. <strong>Polynomial in one variable.</strong></li><li>(iii) $xy + yz + zx$: Contains three variables $x, y, z$. <strong>Polynomial in three variables.</strong></li><li>(iv) $x^2 - 2xy + y^2 + 1$: Contains two variables $x, y$. <strong>Polynomial in two variables.</strong></li></ul>"
        },
        {
