            "solution": "<ul><li>(i) $2x - 1$: Highest power of $x$ is 1. <strong>Degree = 1</strong>.</li><li>(ii) $-10$: Can be written as $-10x^0$. Highest power is 0. <strong>Degree = 0</strong>.</li><li>(iii) $x^3 - 9x + 3x^5$: Highest power of $x$ is 5. <strong>Degree = 5</strong>.</li><li>(iv) $y^3(1 - y^4) = y^3 - y^7$: Highest power of $y$ is 7. <strong>Degree = 7</strong>.</li></ul>"
