            "question": "Find the value of the polynomial $3x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 5$, when $x = 3$ and also when $x = -3$.",
            "solution": "<p>Let $p(x) = 3x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 5$.</p><p>At $x = 3$:</p><p>$p(3) = 3(3)^3 - 4(3)^2 + 7(3) - 5 = 3(27) - 4(9) + 21 - 5 = 81 - 36 + 21 - 5 = 61$.</p><p>At $x = -3$:</p><p>$p(-3) = 3(-3)^3 - 4(-3)^2 + 7(-3) - 5 = 3(-27) - 4(9) - 21 - 5 = -81 - 36 - 21 - 5 = -143$.</p>"
