            "solution": "<p>$p(2) = (2)^2 - 4(2) + 3 = 4 - 8 + 3 = -1$</p><p>$p(-1) = (-1)^2 - 4(-1) + 3 = 1 + 4 + 3 = 8$</p><p>$p(\\frac{1}{2}) = (\\frac{1}{2})^2 - 4(\\frac{1}{2}) + 3 = \\frac{1}{4} - 2 + 3 = \\frac{1}{4} + 1 = \\frac{5}{4}$</p><p>Value = $-1 - 8 + \\frac{5}{4} = -9 + \\frac{5}{4} = \\frac{-36+5}{4} = -\\frac{31}{4}$.</p>"
